STUTTGART SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Stuttgart Solar, LLC ("Stuttgart Solar") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Stuttgart Solar generating facility ("Stuttgart Solar Facility").
The Stuttgart Solar Facility is a photovoltaic solar facility located in Arkansas County, Arkansas. The Stuttgart Solar Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Entergy Arkansas, Inc. and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Stuttgart Solar's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Stuttgart Solar Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Stuttgart Solar's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Stuttgart Solar shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $204,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $17,000.00.
